reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good in theory, less in usage
reviews.reviewText: I have loved packing cubes ever since my friend turned me onto them and gifted me some. The only thing I thought would make them better is some way to compress them so my clothes don't take up as much space. When I saw these compression packing cubes, I thought this was a genius idea.I tried these out on a trip this month and noticed right away issues with the packing and compression portions. My standard packing cubes have a full zip on 3 sides easily opening the flap to pack or unpack. These Tianzong packing cubes only zip to open half the cube meaning you have to slide clothes in instead of place it in, and makes it a bit harder to see or get things depending on how you fold or place things inside (ie socks and underwear).The compression part does zip around to compress the sides but it isn't a magic zipper or vacuums the air out. Even if you fill the packing cube full, it is hard to use the compression zipper if your clothes are thick. I could only close it when I packed in less or packed thinner clothing.The quality also isn't great. The zippers feel like they could break at any time depending how hard I pull or try to compress, and the fabric is rather thin. I can see myself only using these on underwear and thin clothes moving forward.
